1. Copy contents of repository to new folder (except for .git related files). Make sure to copy the .dockerignore file! 
2. Move .env.template to .env
3. Fill out .env variables
4. Build docker image with 'docker build -t kettlewright .'
5. Run 'docker run -it --env-file .env -v $(pwd)/instance:/app/instance kettlewright /bin/sh'
6. Then run 'flask db upgrade' from the shell, then 'exit'
7. Lunch the application with 'docker run --user $(id -u):$(id -g) -v $(pwd)/instance:/app/instance --env-file .env -p 5000:5000 kettlewright'
8. Access the Kettlewright at http://127.0.0.1:5000
